  "comment": "[gof-patterns] Defines context node structure for Zig, handling LOD levels, embeddings, and metadata extraction.",
  "detail": "# Module: context_node.zig — Semantic Entity Management for AI Knowledge Graphs\n\n## Overview and Architecture\n\nThis module provides a type-safe abstraction layer for managing semantic entities (ContextNodes) in an AI coding assistant's knowledge graph. It bridges database operations with application logic by offering two primary capabilities: **type-safe JSON extraction helpers** and a **multi-level-of-detail entity structure**.\n\nThe architecture follows a clean separation between data representation (`ContextNode`) and utility functions (`col*` extractors), enabling reusable patterns across the codebase for database row processing.\n\n## Key Abstractions\n\n### ContextNode\nThe central semantic entity representing any knowledge item in the system:\n- **LOD Pyramid**: Six hierarchical text levels from `lod[0]` (max detail/full description) through `lod[5]` (minimal/alias)\n- **Embedding Vector**: Float32 array for semantic similarity operations\n- **Metadata**: Temporal validity windows, confidence scores, and provenance tracking\n\n### NodeId\nA u64 type matching the database's native integer representation, ensuring type safety across DB boundaries.\n\n### Extraction Helpers\nFive specialized functions that convert `std.json.Value` cells to native Zig types:\n- `colStr`: String extraction with allocator ownership\n- `colFloat`: F64 extraction with default fallback\n- `colOptFloat`: Optional float handling null values explicitly\n- `colBool`: Boolean extraction accepting both bool and integer (0/1) representations\n- `colInt`: Integer extraction supporting both int and float inputs\n\n## Public API Usage Patterns\n\n### Database Row Extraction\n```zig\nconst row = try db.fetchRow(\"SELECT * FROM nodes WHERE id = ?\", id);\nconst name = colStr(allocator, row.get(\"name\"));\nconst score = colFloat(row.get(\"score\"), 0.0);\nconst active = colBool(row.get(\"active\"), true);\n```\n\n### ContextNode Lifecycle\n```zig\nvar node = try ContextNode.init(id, full_text, allocator);\n// Use node...\ndefer node.free(allocator);\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n- **Ownership Tracking**: The `lod_owned` bitmask prevents double-free errors by tracking which LOD slots contain allocator-owned strings versus string literals\n- **Default Values**: All extraction helpers accept defaults for null/missing data, eliminating repeated null checks at call sites\n- **Temporal Integrity**: `valid_from` and `valid_to` enable time-based entity relevance filtering\n\n## Design Patterns\n\n1. **Type-Safe Extractors**: Single-responsibility functions eliminate boilerplate across the codebase\n2. **Builder Pattern**: `init()` constructs a valid node with proper initialization\n3. **LOD Pyramid**: Multi-granularity representation for efficient retrieval at different detail levels\n4. **Bitmask Ownership**: Efficient tracking of allocator state without overhead",
  "keywords": ["ContextNode", "LOD pyramid", "embedding vector", "JSON extraction", "colStr", "colFloat", "colBool", "colInt", "knowledge graph", "semantic entity"],
